A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing May 2025 as Osteoporosis Awareness and Prevention Month; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, an estimated 54 million Americans have osteoporosis or low bone mass, and
4 studies suggest that approximately 1 in 2 women and up to 1 in 4 men age 50 and older will
5 break a bone due to osteoporosis; and
6 WHEREAS, around 1.8 million Medicare beneficiaries suffer approximately 2.1 million
7 osteoporosis-related fractures annually, and osteoporosis-related bone fractures are
8 responsible for more hospitalizations than heart attacks, strokes, or breast cancer; and
9 WHEREAS, the total annual cost for osteoporosis-related fractures among Medicare
10 beneficiaries was $57 billion in 2018, and that number is expected to grow to over $95
11 billion in 2040 without reforms as the population ages; and
12 WHEREAS, in Georgia, over 48,000 Medicare beneficiaries suffered more than 56,400
13 osteoporosis-related fractures in 2016; and
